name: Honeycomb V3PO RESTCONF calls
description: Common mgmt operations on VPP core using Honeycomb REST interface

folders.name: IETF ACL
folders.description: Provides example requests for ietf-access-control-list management

requests.name: Ip Neighbour Get
requests.description: This call returns data stored in honeycomb,to verify actual data stored by vpp, call vppctl show ip fib|arp

requests.name: Ip Neighbour Delete
requests.description: Verify this call by invoking vppctl show ip fib|arp

requests.name: Ip Neighbour Add
requests.description: This call doesnt have respective dump call,because of performance issues(dump for this can contain millions of entries). Data inserted throught this call can be verified by calling vppctl show ip fib|arp

requests.name: Enable GigabitEthernet0/9/0 interface - cfg
requests.description:
Enables GigabitEthernet0/9/0 interface. Equivalent vppctl command:

vppctl set in state GigabitEthernet0/9/0 up

Needed to enable sub interface.

To verify invoke:

vppctl show int

requests.name: Enable L3 IP4 ACL on local0 interface
requests.description:
Creates chain of classfy tabless/sessions in VPP and assigns them to local0 interface.

Can be verified with:
vppctl show classify table verbose

then:
vppctl show inacl type ip4

requests.name: Remove local0 from bridge domain
requests.description:
Removes l2 interconnection of bridge-based type from local0 interface.
Corresponds to the following VAT command:

vat# sw_interface_set_l2_bridge sw_if_index 0 bd_id 1 disable

Verification in VAT:

vat# bridge_domain_dump

requests.name: Modify vhost user ifc - cfg
requests.description:
Modifies vhost-user interface socket.
To verify invoke:

vppctl show vhost-user

requests.name: Enable L2 and Ipv4 ACL on local0 interface
requests.description:
Enables L2 and Ipv4 ACL on local0. Corresponding vpp cli commands:

set int input acl intfc local0 l2-table 0

set int input acl intfc local0 ip4-table 0

To verify invoke:

vppctl show inacl type l2

then:

vppctl show inacl type ip4

requests.name: Disable ACL on local0 interface
requests.description:
Disables ACL on local0. To verify invoke:

vppctl show inacl type l2

and:

vppctl show inacl type ip4

requests.name: Set vrf id for local0 - cfg
Add classify table1
requests.description:
Adds classify table1 chained to classify table0.

Corresponding vpp cli command:

vppctl classify table mask l2 dst next-table 0

To verify invoke:

vppctl sh class table verbose

or:

vat# classify_table_info table_id 1

requests.name: List disabled interfaces - context
requests.description: List disabled interfaces (e.g. deleted vxlan tunnels)

requests.name: Show local0 - oper
requests.description: Shows local0 interface operational state

requests.name: Enable tag-rewrite push - cfg
requests.description:
Enables tag-rewrite push operation for GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 sub-interface. Corresponsing vpp cli command:

vppctl set interface l2 tag-rewrite GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 push dot1q 123 456

To verify run:
./build-root/install-vpp-native/vpp-api-test/bin/vpp_api_test json
and invoke:

#vat sw_interface_dump

or if sub-interface was added to bridge domain:

vppctl show bridge-domain [bd_id] detail

requests.name: List naming contexts - context
requests.description: List mapping context stored in context datastore

requests.name: Delete L2 FIB entry
requests.description:
Removes L2 FIB entry. Corresponds to invoking:

vppctl l2fib del aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff [bd_id]

To verify run:

vppctl show l2fib verbose

requests.name: Add proxy arp on interface
requests.description: Add proxy arp on interface

requests.name: Enable L2 aACL on local0 interface
requests.description:
Creates chain of classfy tabless/sessions in VPP and assigns them to local0 interface.

Can be verified with:
vppctl show classify table verbose

then:
vppctl show inacl type l2

requests.name: Disable tag-rewrite - cfg
requests.description:
Disables tag-rewrite operation for GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 sub-interface. Corresponsing vpp cli command:

vppctl set interface l2 tag-rewrite GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 disable

To verify run:
./build-root/install-vpp-native/vpp-api-test/bin/vpp_api_test json
and invoke:

#vat sw_interface_dump

or if sub-interface was added to bridge domain:

vppctl show bridge-domain [bd_id] detail

requests.name: Disable ACLs on local0
requests.description:
Disables all ACLs assigned to local0 interface.

To verify, invoke:

vppctl show classify table verbose

and:

vppctl show inacl type l2
vppctl show inacl type ip4
vppctl show inacl type ip6

requests.name: Set interfaces bulk edit - cfg
Create bridge domain - cfg
requests.description:
Creates bridgfe domain. Corresponds to invoking:

vat#  bridge_domain_add_del bd_id [bd_id] learn 0 forward 0 uu-flood 0 flood 1 arp-term 0

To verify run:

vppctl show bridge-domain [bd_id] detail

requests.name: Enable tag-rewrite translate 1-2 - cfg
requests.description:
Enables tag-rewrite translate 1-2 operation for GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 sub-interface. Corresponsing vpp cli command:

vppctl set interface l2 tag-rewrite GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 translate 1-2 dot1q 111 222

To verify run:
./build-root/install-vpp-native/vpp-api-test/bin/vpp_api_test json
and invoke:

or if sub-interface was added to bridge domain:

requests.name: Add L2 FIB entry (forward)
requests.description:

requests.name: Add sub interface - cfg
requests.description:
Adds sub interface. Corresponsing vpp cli command:

vppctl create sub GigabitEthernet0/9/0 1 dot1q 100 inner-dot1q any

To verify run:
./build-root/install-vpp-native/vpp-api-test/bin/vpp_api_test json
and invoke:

#vat sw_interface_dump

requests.name: Delete vhost user ifc - cfg
requests.description:
Deletes vhost user interface.
Corresponding vpp CLI command:

To verify invoke:

or

requests.name: Add vhost user ifc - cfg
requests.description:

Corresponsing vpp cli command:

create vhost-user socket /tmp/soc1 server

To verify invoke:

vppctl show vhost-user

or

requests.name: Enable GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 interface - cfg
requests.description:
Enables GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 sub interface. Equivalent vppctl command:

To enable sub interface, super interface should be enabled first.

To verify invoke:

vppctl show int

To verify invoke:
